                    justice, hospitality, oaths. Husband of Hera.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üëë</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Hera</h3>
                    <p>Queen of the gods, goddess of marriage, women, childbirth, and family. Zeus's wife and sister,
                    often portrayed opposing his affairs.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üî±</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Poseidon</h3>
                    <p>God of the sea, earthquakes, and horses. Brother of Zeus, wielded trident, lived primarily
                    in underwater palace but maintained Olympian seat.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üåæ</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Demeter</h3>
                    <p>Goddess of agriculture, harvest, grain, and fertility of the earth. Mother of Persephone,
                    controlled the seasons through grief and joy.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">‚öîÔ∏è</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Ares</h3>
                    <p>God of war, violence, and bloodlust. Son of Zeus and Hera, lover of Aphrodite,
                    represented brutal aspect of warfare.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">ü¶â</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Athena</h3>
