                    twin of Artemis, patron of Delphi.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üèπ</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Artemis</h3>
                    <p>Goddess of hunt, wilderness, wild animals, moon, and chastity. Twin of Apollo,
                    virgin goddess, protector of young girls.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üî•</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Hephaestus</h3>
                    <p>God of fire, metalworking, craftsmanship, and forges. Son of Hera, thrown from Olympus,
                    crafted divine weapons and palaces.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üíï</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Aphrodite</h3>
                    <p>Goddess of love, beauty, pleasure, and procreation. Born from sea foam, married to Hephaestus,
                    lover of Ares and mortals.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üé≠</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Hermes</h3>
                    <p>God of trade, thieves, travelers, sports, athletes, and guide to Underworld. Messenger of gods,
                    son of Zeus, wore winged sandals.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deity-card">
                    <div style="font-size: 3rem;">üçá</div>
                    <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin: 1rem 0;">Dionysus</h3>
                    <p>God of wine, vegetation, pleasure, festivity, madness, and theater. Son of Zeus and mortal Semele,
                    youngest Olympian, replaced Hestia.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(var(--color-primary-rgb), 0.1); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
                <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Note on the Twelve:</h3>
                <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                    The canonical twelve varied across time and region. <strong>Hestia</strong> (goddess of hearth and home)
